The United States has strongly condemned the recent terrorist attacks in Kenya and Somalia. These include an attack on a guest house in Mandera, Kenya, that resulted in approximately 12 deaths, as well as attacks in Northeast Kenya and Somalia, including an attack on Djiboutian forces in the African Union Mission in Somalia. The United States expresses its condolences to the victims and their families and pledges to stand with the people of Kenya and Somalia in their efforts to enhance security and create more opportunities for their citizens. The U.S. will continue to collaborate with regional governments and the African Union Mission in Somalia to defeat terrorist groups and promote regional stability.